e is behind in class. This would not happen if the class sizes were small and the students grouped based on ability. I do not think anyone other than a politician (enemy) would not want this (5 students per class). You say that you don't want this? It is only because you think that we do not have the money for this. Well maybe we should not spend trillions of dollars on bombs and wars etc...!! If we educated all student (including students of color--wow what a unique idea) then we will need less police, less judges, less court officers, less prisons!!! and the list goes on. Of course we will also needs jobs for this well educated citizens! We as a society should do things for the majority of people, not for the top one percent. That is why I am a revolutionary socialist! "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1089" language="en" documentId="3460" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Kohls -" date="Aug 29, 2013 7:09PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="2" thumbsDown="0" origId="3460" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1089"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>